SIMPLE: eddy
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eddy
<hw>Ed"dy</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧d"d⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Eddies</plw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧d"d⟦icr⟧z)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[Prob. fr. Icel. <ets>i⟦edh⟧a</ets>; cf. Icel. pref.
<ets>i⟦edh⟧-</ets> back, AS. <ets>ed-</ets>, OS. <ets>idug-</ets>, OHG.
<ets>ita-</ets>; Goth. <ets>id-</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A current
of air or water running back, or in a direction contrary to the main
current.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A current of water or air moving in a circular
direction; a whirlpool.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And smiling <qex>eddies</qex> dimpled on the main.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wheel through the air, in circling <qex>eddies</qex> play.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>Used also adjectively; as, <xex>eddy</xex> winds.</note>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eddy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Eddy
<hw>Ed"dy</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Eddied</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Eddying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To move as an eddy, or as in an
eddy; to move in a circle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Eddying</qex> round and round they sink.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eddy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Eddy
<hw>Ed"dy</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To collect as into an eddy.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The circling mountains <qex>eddy</qex> in⟦br⟧
From the bare wild the dissipated storm.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eddy current</ent>⟦br⟧
